                        <ul>
                            <li>The Two's complement representation allows =
the use of binary arithmetic operations on signed integers, yielding the co=
rrect 2's complement results. </li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Positive Numbers Positive 2's complement nu=
mbers are represented as the simple binary. </li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Negative Numbers Negative 2's complement nu=
mbers are represented as the binary number that when added to a positive nu=
mber of the same magnitude equals zero. </li>
                        </ul>
