                        <ul>
                            <li>To calculate the 2's complement of an integ=
er, invert the binary equivalent of the number by changing all of the ones =
to zeroes and all of the zeroes to ones (also called 1's complement ), and =
then add one. </li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul>
                            <li>The bit size is always important with twos =
complement, since you must be able to tell where the sign bit is. The steps=
 are simple. </li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul>
